title: Ingrown

thumbnail.alt_text: A work made of chromogenic print, edition number eight of eight.

medium_display: Chromogenic print, edition number eight of eight
credit_line: Gift of Donna and Howard Stone
publication_history:
Nancy Spector, Dan Cameron, Ewa Lajer-Burcharth, Marina Warner, Amy Cappellazzo, and Rosa Martinez, Janine Antoni, (Küsnacht: Ink Tree; New York: Distributed in the US by Distributed Art Publishers, 2000), 96, 97 (color ill.).

Jennifer Blessing, Kirsten A. Hoving, and Ralph Rugoff, Speaking with Hands: Photographs from the Buhl Collection (New York: Solomon R. Guggenheim Foundation, 2004), 161, 162 (color ill.), 200 (color ill.).

James Rondeau and Judith Russi Kirshner, Contemporary Collecting: the Donna and Howard Stone Collection, exh. cat. (Chicago: Art Institute of Chicago; New Haven: Yale University Press, 2010), 30 (color ill.), 136 (ill.).

Laura Blereau, Touched: A Space of Relations-an exhibition exploring the sense of touch as a metaphor of bodily presence and an extension across boundary, exh. guide (New York: Bitforms Gallery, 2011), n.p. (color ill).
exhibition_history:
New York, Luhring Augustine, Inaugural Exhibition, May 28-Aug. 15, 1998, no cat. (another edition)

New York, Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum, Speaking with Hands: Photographs from the Buhl Collection, June 4–Sept. 8, 2004, no cat. no. (another edition)

Art Institute of Chicago, Contemporary Collecting: Selections from the Donna and Howard Stone Collection, June 24-Sept. 19, 2010, no cat. no.

New York, Bitforms Gallery, Touched: A Space of Relations, Feb. 26-Apr. 16, 2011, no cat. no. (another edition).
provenance_text: The artist; sold through Luhring Augustine Gallery, New York, to Donna and Howard Stone, Chicago, Jan. 24, 2003 [copy of invoice in curatorial object file]; given to the Art Institute of Chicago, Sept. 13, 2022.
